  "text": "To investigate the transcription levels of RcoC4H in different tissues, the total RNA of each tissue sample was isolated using a CTAB method [CITATION_1] . One-μg of total RNA was reverse-transcribed in an RT system, the Maxime RT premix kit (iNtRON BIOTECHNOLOGY, Seongnam, Korea) for 60 min at 45°C. The PCR reaction was carried out using the Maxime PCR PreMix (i-MAX II) (iNtRON BIOTECHNOL-OGY, Seongnam, Korea) with specific primers of RT-C4Hf (5´-GAGCTTCGAGTACAACTACTACG-3´) and RT-C4Hr (5´-GATCTCTCCTTTCTGCTGAG-3´) under the following conditions: 94ºC for 2 min, 30 cycles of 94ºC for 20 sec, 50ºC for 20 sec, 72ºC for 30 sec, and 72ºC for 5 min. For equal amounts of the total RNA and the efficiency of the cDNA synthesis from different tissues, the intensities of the bands were normalized with an average intensity of the Rubus sp. Histone h3 gene (GenBank accession no. AF304365) products [CITATION_2] . RT-PCR assays were repeated in triplicate from independent mRNA extractions.",
